<h2 id="200">2. Linking a variation to a storage location</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>A variation needs a warehouse and a storage location before you can book stock in. Without a warehouse and a storage location the system does not know where to book the stock and therefore does not book stock. The standard storage location is only a placeholder location and is used if you have not assigned an individual storage location yet. The best is to select one of your storage locations to begin with.</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock important">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-important" title="Important"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Inheriting the variations to variations</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>When you activate a warehouse for a main variation, this setting is inherited to all variations of the item.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Item » Edit item » Open item » Edit variation.</strong></p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>Warehouse</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select a warehouse from the drop-down list.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Add</strong>. <br>
→ The warehouse will be assigned to the variation and you can carry out further settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
