<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-tip" title="Tip"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Hardware for the plentymarkets app</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Check the <a href="/en/basics/first-steps/system-requirements#40">system requirements</a> page of the manual to see current hardware recommendations for booking in items using the plentymarkets app.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="_assigning_rights_for_incoming_items">7.1. Assigning rights for incoming items</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Users with admin rights can book in items in the plentymarkets app by default. Users with the user classes <strong>Variable</strong> and <strong>Logistics</strong> must be assigned the necessary rights.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Assigning users the right to book in items in the plentymarkets app:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Open the menu <strong>System » Settings » User</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the account of the user.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>Right</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>Mobile</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In the <strong>Visible functions</strong> area, activate the option <strong>Incoming items</strong>.<br>
→ The individual rights for booking in items are shown.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>If necessary, assign additional individual rights. Pay attention to the information given in <a href="#table-app-rights-for-incoming-items">Table 7</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
